      3.0 out of 5 stars too expensive
      Reviewed in India on 20 May 2023
      Verified Purchase
      I wish they had offered the same config with AMD CPU but they dont. All wallplug cables for laptop adapter are incompatible with 99.999% of households in india, so you end up buying another adapter or a cable with smaller input plug. when they are charging so much, they should have given that adapter or extra cable compatible with 99..999% of indian households.
      Good luck upgrading SSD or RAM. It has unenecessarily used different types of screws,unlike acer. The backpanel screws themeselves are of 2 different length, few screws are hidden behind a rubber cover, 2 are screws hidden behind 2 bigger rubber white stamps.
      Inside screws are all torx screws, your philips screw driver wont work. The SSD screw is a torx 5 and users on reddit are complaining that it is too cheaply made screw and any attempt to open it with a wrong screw driver will peel it off, which makes it even harden then to add any nvme drive if you want to. So this also means you need to buy 4 things with it.
      1. big wall plug inlet to small adapter
      2. a powerbrick connecting cable with small inlet for carrying, remote, traveling
      3. a special expensive laptop repair screw driver kit which has torx heads, especially torx t5
      4. a set of torx t5 screws (they always come in a pack of too many btw, so no go).
      I advice you to when you buy it, go to a repair shop, ask them to do all your upgrade, get you different brick cable and adapter so that you wont have this hassle.
